Repositories
*******************************
sudo docker images

CONTAINERS
*******************************

RUN
when running a container wit the run command add --name to have a userfriendly name 
-d will run it in the background 
-i will make it interactive

STOP 
can use the id or name to stop a container
sudo docker stop myairflow


LIST containers 
sudo docker container list

LiST Stopped containers 
sudo docker ps -a 

REMOVE a container 
sudo docker rm myairflow


ATTACH vs EXEC??
To connect to a running container we can use ATTACH or EXEC. 
sudo docker exec -it container_name bash


PRUNE

Stopped containers will which have been created with the name tag will fail when you try to run again.  
To avoid that run the prune command

sudo docker container prune


